'''Filippo Scelzo''' (19 April 1900 – 9 October 1980) was an Italian [[film actor]]. He appeared in more than forty films including ''[[Red Passport]]'' in which he played the male lead.<ref>Landy, Marcia. ''The Folklore of Consensus: Theatricality in the Italian Cinema, 1930-1943''. SUNY Press, 1998. p.155.</ref>

==Selected filmography==
* ''[[Loyalty of Love]]'' (1934)
* ''[[Red Passport]]'' (1935)
* ''[[Trial and Death of Socrates]]'' (1939)
* ''[[The Sons of the Marquis Lucera]]'' (1939)
* ''[[Bridge of Glass (film)|Bridge of Glass]]'' (1940)
* ''[[Kean (1940 film)|Kean]]'' (1940)
* ''[[Odessa in Flames]]'' (1942)
* ''[[The White Angel (1943 film)|The White Angel]]'' (1943)
* ''[[Man with the Grey Glove]]'' (1948)
* ''[[Il grido della terra|The Earth Cries Out]]'' (1948)
* ''[[Romanticismo (film)|Romanticismo]]'' (1950)
* ''[[The Ungrateful Heart]]'' (1951)
* ''[[The Shadow (1954 film)|The Shadow]]'' (1954)
* ''[[The Verona Trial]]'' (1963)
* ''[[La corruzione]]'' (1963)

